   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intl. House</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Contribute to filling the gap between supply and demand for quality office space in Bujumbura and provide much needed property infrastructure which is necessary to attract and retain investment in this post conflict country; -	Private sector development, an important engine for growth, in a post-conflict country; - Introduce new building standards to the market;  - Have a demonstration effect on other local companies to pursue similar commercial property development projects; - Create opportunity for linkages and benefit to other sectors of the economy, from suppliers to tenants who will benefit from additional quality office space; -	Create employment (direct and indirect) for about 200 people during construction and about 100 post-construction; -	Increase in government revenues through taxes paid.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PROGIMMO S. A (Progimmo or the Company), a local property developer in Burundi, intends to build and manage a modern office/commercial building in Bujumbura (the Project).  The Project will consist of two three story structures with about 7,000 m2 and adequate parking.  The design of the building will conform to international life, fire and safety standards.</narrative>
  </description>
